Description: This company has patented the only known process to make emission-free power from very low temperature waste heat, 90F and up –even.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: This company has patented the only known process to make emission-free power from very low temperature waste heat, 90F and up –even from intermittent and variable-temperature sources--to produce full time emission free power. Waste heat has long been recognized as a vast energy resource. Waste heat power generation equipment is already a fast-growing industry with players like GE and United Technologies. However, all current technologies require waste heat of 200-500 degrees F or more and most require as found in industrial sites. Most if not all require large amounts of cooling water. Untapped until now is over 1 trillion kWh per year of low-grade waste heat from commercial air conditioning and refrigeration, equal to the heat from over 170,000,000 tons of coal.  Every watt of electricity used for AC/R results in about four watts of this easily captured heat, with a typical temperature of 120 degrees F, varying by time of day and season. This new patented technology uses the intermittent and variable temperature low grade heat. The system uses a new patented mode of heat transfer and recycles its own waste heat.  It does not require cooling water. The technology is scalable for commercial buildings from fast food restaurants to supermarkets and up, opening a new market for U.S. made equipment worth $50 billion and rising.  We have invested over 5 years and over $2M in development to date. Now it is time to take the technology to market in commercial systems.  With patented technology, a proven capital-efficient business model, seasoned management, and a sensible plan, American Thermal Power has enormous upside potential.
Industry Groups: Consumer Electronics, Energy, Hardware, Information Technology

Description: Branded Experience Sharing Platform
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: Add the "where" to your photos and videos! We provide an open, patent-pending technology offering a centralized, location-based set of fun and intriguing visual templates for use with your own personal digital media (primarily photos & videos). These "Place Templates" are provided by each of your favorite places to visit and are visually descriptive of the place itself, including local geography and business artifacts. You can use these Place Templates as: 1) Souvenir which is a "fun" photo coupon that YOU create and send to your friends & family to save them REAL money. This is also known as a "Photopon". 2) Digital "Comic Foreground" photo like from the old days when you'd visit a place that had a themed plywood template for you to place your face in and snap a picture (now modernized and social - but more importantly FUN & ADDICTIVE and all set for robust photo sharing. Our revenue model is comprised of businesses who gladly pay a small subscription fee to host these templates that are accessible to multiple check-in apps (including our own) and that extend brand awareness and promotional efforts in the most cost-efficient and effective (social word-of-mouth through photos). Our system is disruptive by design in that businesses can charge a small fee for some templates (non-branded or branded) which opens the doorway for an entirely new marketplace for both designers and business clients who wish to sell these digital items upon customer check-in. At a higher-level, our parent company - Exlorous - records and mines this data at the human experience level and tracks a whole new experience data set at a place or brand - when someone checks into a place or brand, they are now experiencing the place or brand itself, as well as the intrigue and/or fun in sharing what they're doing. By default, our platform also concurrently promotes customer loyalty by sharing each of these media objects using the templates provided by the very brands they love and the locations they frequent. In summary, we are an "enabler" for extending brand awareness while encouraging friends & family to check out some of the cool new places you've discovered or that you frequent. Content always changes at these locations which further entices visitors to return for new discoveries within the digital spectrum. This product paves the way for an entirely new industry while simultaneously making photo sharing infinitely fun and "SERENDIPITOUS" with the power of new discoveries all around you each and every day and the ability for multiple parties to profit/economically prosper from such an ecosystem :-) (all while data mining for the bigger, strategic picture)
